</p></div>"}

Plant the seedling in the ground when the first set of leaves appear. Lightly crush the eggshell with your hand, and place the eggshell and seedling directly into the ground. Use eggshells to improve compost. Gardeners frequently add lime to compost to correct acidity problems in garden soil. Lime is made up of calcium carbonate, which is the main nutrient in eggshells. Rather than purchase lime, recycle eggshells to amend compost. Crush eggshells and add them directly to the compost. To decrease the decomposition time, dry the eggshells in an oven and grind them using a blender before adding them to the compost. Recycle eggshells as fertilizer for the garden. Eggshells contain calcium, phosphorus, sulfur and potassium, which help make plants healthy. Rinse eggshells. Allow the eggshells to dry, and place them in a bowl or large container. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/71/Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/71/Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Grind the eggshells using a pestle, which is a hand-held tool used for mashing or grinding substances. If you do not have a pestle, grind the eggshells in a blender. The smaller the eggshell pieces, the faster they will break down in the soil. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Recycle-Eggshells-in-Gardening-Activities-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
